Linné Ahlstrand https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linn%C3%A9_Ahlstrand 0 Linné Nanette Ahlstrand (July 1, 1936 – January 18, 1967) was an American model and actress. She was Playboy magazine's Playmate of the Month for its July 1958 issue. Her centerfold was photographed by Frank Bez. Ahlstrand moved to New York City from Hollywood, California. to pursue an acting and modeling career. She appeared in such movies as Living Venus, Beast from Haunted Cave, and in such TV Shows as Highway Patrol, and Johnny Stacatto. She returned to the Los Angeles area in September, 1965, when she got married. Ahlstrand continued to pursue an acting and modeling career before her untimely death to cancer at age 30 in Pasadena, California in 1967.
